# Azveria Online

Azveria Online is a Laravel-based strategy web app with role-based screens for players and admins.

## Core Stack
- Backend API/Auth/Business Rules: Laravel (PHP 8.3)
- Real-time: Ratchet WebSocket server (chat + announcements only)
- Database: MySQL 8
- Containers: Docker Compose on one internal bridge network

## Why WebSocket Is Limited
WebSocket is only used where real-time value is high:
- Global announcements stream
- Group chat / direct message live delivery

Everything else uses REST:
- Nation stats pages
- Map layer metadata and terrain summaries
- Shop listings and purchases
- Settings and help/meta

## Player Navigation

### Player
- Full nation dashboard with:
  - Resources
  - Leader
  - Alliances
  - Terrain percentages (grassland, mountain, fresh water bodies, hills, desert)
  - Units owned and units in training (separated)
  - Buildings and buildings in construction/upgrade (separated)
  - Editable About field with save action

### Announcements
- Read-only global feed for players.
- Admins are the only senders.

### Map
- Center map with zoom + pan interaction.
- Right panel toggle for:
  - Main map
  - Terrain map
  - Political alignment map
- Terrain square mileage summary for current player under the toggle list.

### Chat
- Right side chat list (group + direct).
- Center active conversation.
- Chat creation flow with member selection and custom chat name.

### Other Nations
- Dynamic page based on logged-in user.
- Right panel nation selector.
- Search box with partial substring match on nation name and player name format:
  - NationName (PlayerName)

### Shop
- Right side categories:
  - Refinement
  - Structures
  - Upgrades
  - Recruitment
  - Crafting
- Center list of items with costs and buy action.
- Cost model supports easy expansion beyond Cow, Wood, Ore, Food.

### Settings
- Light / dark mode.
- Color blindness modes.
- Optional goofy sound on user actions.
- Separate Font Mode selector (normal / fun / cool person).

### Help Dropdown
- About
- Documentation (opens repository README)
- Logout

## Persistent Top Bar Resource Display
Every player screen includes current:
- Cow
- Wood
- Ore
- Food

## Data Foundations
Source content has been mapped from your Azveria files into the backend design:
- Rules and resources
- Structures and terrain
- War and army behavior
- Dakotians unit examples

## Project Files
- Docker stack: `docker-compose.yml`
- SQL schema: `database/init/001_schema.sql`
- Backend architecture: `docs/backend-blueprint.md`
- Ratchet service: `backend/websocket/server.php`

## Quick Start
1. Start services:
	- `docker compose up -d --build`
2. Create Laravel app folder (first run only):
	- `docker compose exec app composer create-project laravel/laravel .`
3. Copy env:
	- `cp backend/.env.example backend/laravel/.env`
4. Generate app key:
	- `docker compose exec app php artisan key:generate`
5. Run migrations (if moving schema from SQL into Laravel migrations):
	- `docker compose exec app php artisan migrate`

## Next Implementation Milestones
